  "prompt": "Will it be fine if both husband and wife having same blood group?",
  "response": "Yes, it is completely fine if both husband and wife have the same blood group. The compatibility of blood groups is more relevant when it comes to blood transfusions rather than marriage or having children. What is important for pregnancy is the Rh factor, which can impact the mother's health and pregnancy if there is an incompatibility. If both partners have the same Rh factor (either both positive or both negative), there generally won't be any Rh-related issues during pregnancy.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about blood groups and pregnancy, it may be best to consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice.",
